timedatectl --> Shows Time and Timezone

NTP - Network Time Protocol -> With This our Computer will contact time server and fetch the time from there
timedatectl set-ntp true  --> Turning on ntp for timedate ctl


date --> Show the local date and time
date --utc  --> Shows Universal Date and time

date +"%h %d %y"
date +"%s"  --> This shows the No of sec since 1 Jan 1970
This can be used in Script for calculating the execution time

date -d "+10 days"  --> Shows 10 days after current date
date -d "+1 Year"  

date -d "next thursday --> shows next thursday
date -d "next thursday" +"%s" --> Shows next thursday in sec
